Enpuzzle, here are some building code requirements. All of the products that Corian, Silestone, Quartz, etc. produce are natural stone ground up with a resin added. They all comply with US and Canadian fiberglass/butyl/neoprene acrylic formula made in rolacoat have a polyester resin in them.

While the resins all comply, not all laminate products have the same consistency. Formica is saying that their products are "have the ability to bond together and laminate together,not that it is made of laminate product.
